International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 29 Dec 2011
Source: Gideon [edited]
http://www.gideononline.com


Rates of brucellosis in Argentina have been decreasing for over 2
decades but continue to parallel those reported in the USA during the
1950s (1,2), as can be seen on the graph (3):
http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Brucella-Argentina.png.

References
----------
1. Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of Argentina, 2011. 417 pp, 96
graphs, 1516 references. Gideon e-books,
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-argentina/.
